{"key":"post-6046380","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6046380</id>\n<content>Perlite should be rinsed under the faucet in a strainer, then when it's drained well dumped into the terrarium.  This will provide proper humidity for at least three weeks.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Condensation on the sides is an indication of a temperature differential between inside and outside the terrarium and has absolutely nothing to do with humidity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If your humidity is too low, the mushrooms will have cracked caps, that resemble mud when it dries out and cracks in the summer sun.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6046417</next>\n<prev>6046377</prev>\n<first>6046346</first>\n<last>6046417</last>\n<when>1157907786</when>\n<utime>09/10/06 08:03 PM</utime>\n</post>"}